      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2000_Problems_2000_page_001_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–6 Let f (x) be a polynomial with integer coefficients. De- fine a sequence ao, a1, . .. of integers such that ao = 0 and an+1 = f (an) for all n ≥ 0. Prove that if there exists a positive integer m for which am = 0 then either a1 = 0 or a2 = 0.",
        "bbox": [
          0.09333333333333334,
          0.4812121212121212,
          0.49019607843137253,
