        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B–6 Let B be a set of more than 2n+1/n distinct points with coordinates of the form (±1, ±1, . ., ±1) in n- dimensional space with n ≥ 3. Show that there are three distinct points in B which are the vertices of an equilat- eral triangle.",
